            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p><strong>Where Anyword wins:</strong> if your bottleneck is ad CTR or email open rate, the Predictive Score is the only AI tool feature that genuinely moves the metric. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> if your bottleneck is organic traffic and you need content published consistently to your CMS.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is Anyword?</h2>
        <p>Anyword was founded in 2013 in Tel Aviv (originally as Keywee) and pivoted to AI copywriting in 2020. The company has raised <strong>~$30M</strong> in funding and counts <strong>Ted Baker, Hasbro, IBM, and Greenpeace</strong> as enterprise customers. The thesis: every other AI writer generates copy; only Anyword tells you which generation will perform best.</p>

        <p>The product splits into five modules:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Predictive Performance Score</strong> — 1–100 score on every generated piece, trained on billions of ad impressions</li>
          <li><strong>Ad copy generator</strong> — Meta, Google, LinkedIn, TikTok formats with character-limit awareness</li>
          <li><strong>Email + landing page</strong> — subject lines, body copy, CTAs scored for predicted CTR</li>
          <li><strong>Brand voice</strong> — clone your existing copy's tone (Pro tier+)</li>
          <li><strong>Custom audiences</strong> — calibrate the score against your historical ad performance (Data-Driven tier)</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What Anyword is <em>not</em>: an SEO blog writer, a rank tracker, a publishing platform, or a content optimization tool. It is performance copy, period.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Company background</div>
          <p>Founded by Yaniv Makover (CEO) and Yannai Levin in Tel Aviv. The original product, Keywee, was a content-distribution platform for publishers. The 2020 pivot to AI copywriting came out of the predictive models built for Keywee's ad-targeting. That training data — billions of ad impressions across hundreds of brands — is the moat that makes the Predictive Score work.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">Anyword features — the 2026 walkthrough</h2>

        <h3>1. Predictive Performance Score — the differentiator</h3>
        <p>Every generated piece of copy gets a 1–100 score plus a target-audience breakdown (gender, age, persona). The score is trained on billions of ad impressions, so it correlates with actual CTR — not just "this sounds good." In our tests, copy scoring 80+ outperformed copy scoring &lt;60 by 30–40% in Meta Ads CTR. Real-world useful.</p>

        <h3>2. Ad copy generator</h3>
        <p>Format-aware generation for Meta (single image, carousel, story, reels), Google (RSAs with 15 headlines + 4 descriptions), LinkedIn, TikTok, X (Twitter), Pinterest. The character-limit awareness is the small detail that matters — no more 240-character LinkedIn headlines that get truncated. Output is tighter than Jasper for this use case.</p>

        <h3>3. Email + landing page</h3>
        <p>Subject-line generator with predicted open-rate scores. Body-copy generator with CTA suggestions. Landing-page section drafting (hero, features, FAQs, footer). Solid for marketing teams running drip campaigns or A/B testing landing pages.</p>

        <h3>4. Brand voice (Pro+)</h3>
        <p>Upload 5–10 existing pieces of copy and Anyword extracts the tone, sentence structure, and vocabulary. Output future copy in that voice. Comparable to Jasper's Brand Voice — slightly less accurate but usable.</p>

        <h3>5. Custom audiences (Data-Driven+)</h3>
        <p>Connect Meta Ads or Google Ads. Anyword imports your historical performance and calibrates the Predictive Score against your specific audience — not the global benchmark. This is the feature that justifies the $79/mo Data-Driven tier for any account spending $1K+/mo on paid.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">Anyword pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead><tr><th>Plan</th><th>Monthly</th><th>Annual / mo</th><th>Words</th><th>Best for</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Starter</strong></td><td>$49/mo</td><td>$39/mo</td><td>20k</td><td>Solo marketer trial</td></tr>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Data-Driven</strong></td><td>$99/mo</td><td>$79/mo</td><td>30k</td><td>Most paid users land here</td></tr>
