        <h2 id="verdict">Is Anyword worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For paid-ad marketers: yes — Data-Driven tier is the right call.</strong> $79/mo with Meta + Google Ads integration calibrates the Predictive Score against your audience. 30–40% CTR uplift on high-scoring copy is real and repeatable. The score is the only AI-tool feature we have tested that consistently moves a real-world metric.</p>

        <p><strong>For SEO content teams: no — wrong tool.</strong> The Predictive Score is calibrated for ad clicks, not search rankings. Long-form blog output is generic. There is no keyword research, no rank tracking, no CMS publishing. Use Jasper or theStacc instead.</p>

        <p><strong>For small businesses without ad spend: skip.</strong> The score is the entire value prop. If you have no paid budget to validate it against, you are paying $39–$79/mo for slightly-better-than-average AI copy.</p>

